{{Infobox Hieroglyphs Two-Column
|TITLE = Ta-djeser
|EXTENDED NAME = {{ill|New Kingdom|de|Neues Reich|ja|新王国|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}
|NAME = <hiero>N16:D45</hiero><br/>Ta-djeser<br/>''T3-ḏsr''<br/>''Holy Land'' /<br/>''Land of Light'' /<br/>''Forbidden Land of the Living'' /<br/>''Realm of the Dead''
}}

'''Ta-djeser''' is the {{ill|Ancient Egypt|de|Altes Ägypten|ja|古代エジプト|lt=ancient Egyptian|lt_de=altägyptische|lt_ja=古代エジプト的|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} designation for the '''Land of Light''' in the {{ill|Duat|de|Duat|ja|ドゥアト|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. In {{ill|Egyptian Mythology|de|Ägyptische Mythologie|ja|エジプト神話|lt=Egyptian mythological|lt_de=ägyptischen Mythologie|lt_ja=エジプト神話的|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, Ta-djeser was regarded as the assigned region for the deceased, who, following the positive verdict of the {{ill|Judgment of the Dead|de|Totengericht|ja|死者の審判|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, reached it by crossing the sacred subterranean lake of purification.

Reports from the {{ill|Book of Nut|de|Nutbuch|ja|ヌトの書|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} reveal that the gods regenerated as {{ill|Chatiu Demons|de|Chatiu-Dämonen|ja|チャティウ・デーモン|lt=Chatiu|lt_de=Chatiu|lt_ja=チャティウ|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} in the realm of the dead, to later be reborn together with {{ill|Re (Egyptian Mythology)|de|Re (ägyptische Mythologie)|ja|ラー (エジプト神話)|lt=Re|lt_de=Re|lt_ja=ラー|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.

== See also ==
* {{ill|Sechet-iaru|de|Sechet-iaru|ja|セヘト・イアル|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}

== Literature ==
* {{ill|Alexandra von Lieven|de|Alexandra von Lieven|ja|アレクサンドラ・フォン・リーベン|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}: ''Outline of the Course of the Stars – The so-called Book of Nut''. The Carsten Niebuhr Institute of Ancient Eastern Studies (among others), Copenhagen 2007, ISBN 978-87-635-0406-5
* Alexandra von Lieven: ''The Sky over Esna – A Case Study in Religious Astronomy in Egypt Using the Example of the Cosmological Ceiling and Architrave Inscriptions in the Temple of Esna''. Harrassowitz, Wiesbaden 2000, ISBN 3-447-04324-5.
